EFF leader, Julius Malema has refused to give a warning statement to the Hawks after he was summoned to the unit's headquarters in Pretoria. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - EFF leader, Julius Malema has refused to give a sworn statement to the Hawks after he was summoned to the unit's headquarters in Pretoria on Tuesday. READ: Malema begs for forgiveness from other Africans The refusal was in relation to an incident where Malema was filmed seemingly firing a rifle into the air during an EFF rally last year. Malema said the Hawks were being "mischievous" and "dramatic" and said the party would deal with the matter if the police decided to proceed with the case.